Trim the @green beans{150%g} then chop into thirds.

Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}. Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g can}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #saucepan{} over medium high heat.

When hot add the @Massaman Curry Paste{50%g} and the @peanut butter{1%tsp}, cook,
stirring, until aromatic, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @coconut milk{200%ml}, @vegetable stock powder{1%tsp}, green beans,
chickpeas and @water{100%ml}, bring to the boil, then stir in the
@king prawns{150%g} and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes}.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, mix well and bring to a simmer.
Lower the heat, cover with a #lid{} (or some #tin foil{}) and simmer until the
green beans are tender and the prawns are cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the
> centre.

Meanwhile, cook the @steamed basmati rice{1%pack} according to pack instructions.

Taste the curry and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed.

Stir through half the lime zest and add a squeeze of lime juice.

Divide the rice between #bowls{} and top with the curry. Sprinkle over the
remaining lime zest and serve with lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!